Pokemon Sword - 8 badges, won the Championship, explores every town in UNDER 35 HOURS.

Shame on you Game-freak. This game was truly awful, worst Pokédex, terrible story with no real antagonist or any real story events, and the worst Pokédex ever filled with horrible new Pokémon designs and stupid ass food Pokémon. DO NOT BUY THE DLC. Go play any of the wonderful games made before Sun/Moon. You will gets hundreds of hours of nostalgia and enjoyment. Hundreds of Pokémon to catch and evolve. And dozens of interesting places to explore.

I wasnt expecting Sword and Shield to be great, but I also wasn’t expecting it to be this terrible.

snippet.textDisplay:
This is a growing pattern that I found. Every time I put focus on and play a classic game, a remake for that classic game gets announced. This happened with the Mario & Luigi games. Now this.
NINTENDO!!! A new Pokémon Ranger game.
Hopefully a new Pokémon Ranger game is near.
Plus...all the nods at/references to Pokémon Ranger - Guardian Signs (in Pokémon Sun/Moon and Pokémon Ultra Sun/Ultra Moon) would be reasoned.
- The Alola Islands resemble Oblivia from Guardian Signs somewhat.
- Riding Pokémon through the region is another nod
Nintendo! It's about time!! Bring back Pokémon Ranger!!
My weird classic play then remake announcement "coincidence" happened with Link's Awakening DX too. Imagine that.
